-- Hong Kong government says has no plan to ease property cooling measures 
-- 
-- Wed May 21, 2014 09:34PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, May 22 (Reuters) - The Hong Kong government said on Thursday it has no intention of easing property cooling measures in the city, where prices have surged nearly 120 percent since 2008 due to an ultra-low interest rate environment, tight supply and abundant liquidity.

